  "texts": [
    "In each iteration, another for loop is executed that executes the timestamp function in each iteration with a total of INNER LOOP COUNT iterations.",
    "After that another loop with the same number of iterations is run but no operation is executed in it.",
    "So, by getting the time before and after its execution, the overhead of a for loop is in hand.",
    "By subtracting the values, we get INNER LOOP COUNT times the overhead of the timestamp function.",
    "Then, we wait for one millisecond to execute the next iteration of the outer loop."
  ],
